Sat Mar 21 00:53:32 UTC 2026 - Shawn Dunn <sfalken@opensuse.org>

- Update to 0.7.1:
  * Adds CPU, memory, and network usage graph dockapps
    (gh#phkaeser/wlmaker#431)
  * add clipboard support (gh#phkaeser/wlmaker#399)
  * Sets the default style to be more aligned with GNUStep and with
    gray background (gh#phkaeser/wlmaker#446)
  * Read keymap from /etc/default/keyboard or similar
  * Adds wlmtool to parse XDG desktop files, eliminates need for
    wmmenugen
  * Build with wlroots-0.20
  * Refactors pointer focus and layout computation to compute only
    once per frame
  * BugFixes:
    - Fix crash when changing to different terminal
      (gh#phkaeser/wlmaker#438)
    - wlmaker not showing window of wlroots clients
      (gh#phkaeser/wlmaker#439)
    - Cursor remains small (not scaled) on output with scale > 1.0
      (gh#phkaeser/wlmaker#444)
  * Added 0002-allow-for-config-in-usr-etc.patch
  * Updated libbase to a6c6a27e1f8fa2af3b36e9b2f60dbc0bfa0bcb0e

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Mon Jan 26 00:26:46 UTC 2026 - Shawn Dunn <sfalken@opensuse.org>

- Update to 0.7:
  * Output state and Window fixes
  * Updates CMake version tag and header in roadmap
- Updates from 0.5 - 0.6.2
  * Support for multiple outputs, configurable through
    wlr-output-management-unstable-v1 protocol
  * Root Menu can be generated from XDG repository
  * wlmclock now keeps updating also on accelerated graphics
    backends
  * Fixes crash with root menu open and output magnify/removal
  * Fixed build issues on Ubuntu
- Added 0001-remove-google-chrome.patch
- Updated bundled libbase library to aa0da7a355b04b1dd8572a94261a0b0c497e1a85

